                        <div class="lb-xb-grid lb-row-max-large lb-snap lb-vgutter-collapse lb-tiny-xb-1 lb-small-xb-2">
                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                <figure class="lb-svg">
                                    <div>

                                </figure>
                                <h3 id="Learn_About_AWS_Pricing" class="lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-h3 lb-title"> <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/pricing/?nc2=h_ql_pr"> Learn About AWS Pricing</a> </h3>
                                <div class="lb-txt-none lb-txt">
                                    With AWS, you pay only for the individual services you need for as long as you use them without requiring long-term contracts or complex licensing
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                <figure class="lb-svg">
                                    <div>
                                        <img src="./awsamazoncom_files/nav-illo_pricing_free-tier_120.c97a7bc66fe2ed5fe4ace6898dda6783872228e6.svg">
                                    </div>
                                </figure>
                                <h3 id="AWS_Free_Tier" class="lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-h3 lb-title"> <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/free/?nc2=h_ql_pr"> AWS Free Tier</a> </h3>
                                <div class="lb-txt-none lb-txt">
                                    AWS Free Tier includes offers that are always free, offers that expire 12 months following sign up, and short-term free trial offers
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                                                <div class="lb-col lb-tiny-24 lb-mid-4">
                                                    <h1 id="1" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-blue-black lb-tiny-v-margin lb-h1-large lb-title"> 1</h1>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-col lb-tiny-24 lb-mid-20">

                                        <a style="padding-bottom:0px;" href="https://aws.amazon.com/getting-started/tutorials/?sc_icampaign=acq_aws_takeover-1st-visit&amp;sc_ichannel=ha&amp;sc_icontent=awssm-evergreen-1st-visit&amp;sc_iplace=ed&amp;trk=ha_awssm-evergreen-1st-visit">
                                            <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-grid lb-row lb-row-max-large lb-snap lb-collapse">
                                                <div class="lb-col lb-tiny-24 lb-mid-4">
                                                    <h1 id="2" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-blue-black lb-tiny-v-margin lb-h1-large lb-title"> 2</h1>
                                                </div>

                                        <div class="lb-xb-grid lb-row-max-large lb-snap lb-tiny-xb-1 lb-mid-xb-2 lb-large-xb-4">
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-F1-1-mobile-beginning-a-transformation-ending" title="PI-F1-1-mobile-beginning-a-transformation-ending" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-F1-1-mobile-beginning-a-transformation-ending.4af343da1046d7e45d0a44101a57ab2c9544861d.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Beginning_a_Transformation" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> Beginning a Transformation</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Formula One Group is moving most of its infrastructure from on-premises data centers to AWS and standardizing on AWS machine-learning servicesincluding Amazon SageMaker.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-F1-2-mobile-optimizing-racing-machine-learning-ending" title="PI-F1-2-mobile-optimizing-racing-machine-learning-ending" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-F1-2-mobile-optimizing-racing-machine-learning-ending.22f98b262d8569b74c019b78fdfcbd85a3f356cb.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Optimizing_Racing_with_Machine_Learning" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Optimizing Racing with Machine Learning</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Using historical race data collected from cars over the past 65 years, Formula 1 data scientists are training deep-learning models that make race predictions and help teams optimize mid-race decisions. The models can predict when teams should pit their cars, determine the best timing for changing tires, and evaluate how drivers are performing.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-F1-3-mobile-bringing-fans-into-the-track-ending" title="PI-F1-3-mobile-bringing-fans-into-the-track-ending" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-F1-3-mobile-bringing-fans-into-the-track-ending.6df5cc0847826ccd6e20f9aea0f57e179f5fd929.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Bringing_Fans_onto_the_Track" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Bringing Fans onto the Track</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Formula 1 then uses AWS data streaming, analytics, and media services to deliver insights about driver decisions and car performance to its more than 500 million fans.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-F1-4-mobile-building-for-the-future-ending" title="PI-F1-4-mobile-building-for-the-future-ending" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-F1-4-mobile-building-for-the-future-ending.89056dfe247e984e3cb99ea2a84bf31c6ab780dd.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Building_for_the_Future" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Building for the Future</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Because Formula 1 runs its high-performance computing workloads in a scalable environment on AWS, the organization can innovate on the Formula 1 racing experience, car design, and more without worrying about capacity.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>

                                    <h2 id="Intuit_Makes_Tax_Filing_Less_Taxing_Using_AWS" class="lb-tiny-align-left lb-txt-normal lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-txt-28 lb-h2 lb-title"> Intuit Makes Tax Filing Less Taxing Using AWS</h2>
                                    <div class="lb-tiny-align-left lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-txt-16 lb-txt-lead lb-txt">
                                        Learn how financial technology company Intuit uses Amazon SageMaker to train its machine learning models quickly and at scale, cutting the time needed to deploy models by 90 percent.
                                    </div>

                                                    <h4 id="Embracing_the_Cloud" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> Embracing the Cloud</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Intuit is all in on AWS and uses a wide breadth of AWS services to provide the elasticity it needs to handle highly seasonal traffic patterns. Since 2013, Intuit has moved its infrastructure, applications, data, and machine learning capabilities to AWS.

                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">

                                                    <h4 id="Amazon_SageMaker_for_Machine_Learning" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Amazon SageMaker for Machine Learning</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/sagemaker/?hp=tile&amp;story=intuit" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon SageMaker</u></b></a>, Intuit has reduced the cost and the time needed to deploy machine learning models. Data scientists can now create a model and scale it out to many servers, and what used to take six months now takes one week.

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="A_Foundation_for_Deep_Learning" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> A Foundation for Deep Learning</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">MLB has been collecting statistical data on its players and clubs for decades, and in 2015 it started using AWS to collect and distribute game-day stats to enhance the fan experience.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Empowering_Developers" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Empowering Developers</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">By using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/sagemaker/?hp=tile&amp;story=mlb" target="_blank"><u><b>Amazon Sagemaker</b></u></a>, MLB is empowering its developers and data scientists to quickly and easily build, train, and deploy machine-learning models at scale.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Lightening_the_Load" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Lightening the Load</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">These models help MLB eliminate manual, time-intensive processes associated with recordkeeping and statistics, like scorekeeping, capturing game notes, and classifying pitches.
                                                        <br> </p>

                                                    <h4 id="Personalizing_the_Game" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Personalizing the Game</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">MLB plans to work with the Amazon ML Solutions Lab to continue improving Statcastits tracking technology that analyzes player performanceincluding testing accuracy of pitch predictions and creating personalized viewer experiences.

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="A_Home_Run_with_Artificial_Intelligence" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> A Home Run with Artificial Intelligence</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">MLB will continue to innovate using artificial intelligence. The organization plans to use <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/comprehend/?hp=tile&amp;story=mlb" target="_blank"><u><b>Amazon Comprehend</b></u></a> to build a language model that could create scripts for live games that simulate iconic announcers.

                                                        </g>
                                                    </g>
                                                </svg>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="lb-xb-grid-wrap" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                        <div class="lb-xb-grid lb-row-max-large lb-snap lb-tiny-xb-1 lb-mid-xb-3 lb-large-xb-6">
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-1" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-1" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-1.36103b2940e41c1b25d4cda508496b5802655cfe.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Real-Time_Container_Tracking" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> Real-Time Container Tracking</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Matson built a flagship mobile application for global container tracking that allows customers to perform real-time tracking of their freight shipments. Other valuable features in the application include interactive vessel schedule searching, location-based port map lookups, and live gate-camera feeds.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-2" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-2" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-2.2923fa87db78f8dc3b173ffeff2e151e6f513008.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Mobile_Device_Access" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Mobile Device Access</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">All mobile devices access AWS via <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/api-gateway/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon API Gateway</u></b></a>. This provides highly available edge located endpoints for access into resources within Matson's existing virtual private clouds.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-3" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-3" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-3.4749edfbaccd0391062f213faa2336a02db27a66.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Serverless_Computing" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Serverless Computing</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">The <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Lambda</u></b></a> functions are designed using the microservices pattern and are modeled around specific ocean-based business contexts, such as shipment tracking and vessel schedules.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-4" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-4" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-4.13867ba3a13b1122d517cfa1f7b753d9082d8e29.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Database_Configuration_and_Storage" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Database Configuration and Storage</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/dynamodb/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon DynamoDB</u></b></a>&nbsp;manages configuration as well as user-feedback&nbsp;configuration and user-feedback notifications sent from mobile devices. DynamoDB Streams provides real-time notifications&nbsp;to Matson's customer service team.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-5" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-5" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-5.df77636ce4806ed66154ee426b575bcf6e94a03a.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Data_Monitoring_and_Alerts" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Data Monitoring and Alerts</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Matson's customers rely on accurate, up-to-the-minute container tracking and vessel status information. Monitoring and alerting of system events is achieved by using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon CloudWatch</u></b></a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/sns/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon SNS</u></b></a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ses/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon SES</u></b></a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/?hp=tile&amp;story=matson" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Lambda</u></b></a>, and CloudWatch Logs.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-6" title="PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-6" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-Matson-Mobile_Step-6.511a30e5aa425a4d0f421a6d47250eaec50a8e92.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="End-to-End_Serverless_Application" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> End-to-End Serverless Application</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">Matson can now offer customers an end-to-end serverless application to help track their shipments, and has no infrastructure&nbsp;to maintain.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </li>

                        IoT

                                    <div class="lb-xb-grid-wrap" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                        <div class="lb-xb-grid lb-row-max-large lb-snap lb-tiny-xb-1 lb-mid-xb-3 lb-large-xb-6">
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-1" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-1" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-1.ad264b59b189164c5d1ec9b9582f200fb52c35bf.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="iRobot_Roomba_900_Completes_Cleaning" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> iRobot Roomba 900 Completes Cleaning</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">The Roomba 900 series completes a cleaning mission in the home and returns to the dock for charging.
                                                        <br> </p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-2" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-2" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-2.13c6c60359767eadd17b094ffb20037d3d0e1d99.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Data_Processing" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Data Processing</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">iRobot processes the home map, calculates the total floor space cleaned and the status code for the cleaning mission, and publishes the metadata to <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/iot-core/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS IoT</u></b></a>.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-3" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-3" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-3.ac5adf3ae6d6ebe927223c4fa3f08bc3cb4402c1.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Data_Streams_Available" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Data Streams Available</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">iRobot uses an AWS IoT rule to put the message into an <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/kinesis/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot" target="_blank"><u><b>Amazon Kinesis</b></u></a> stream. From Kinesis, iRobot can process the cleaning mission data.&nbsp;Kinesis allows multiple teams to receive the stream of data.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-4" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-4" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-4.334079bc1f919b2ab86ba67f652b0bebfa6ed397.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Data_Storage_and_Analysis" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Data Storage and Analysis</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Lambda</u></b></a>&nbsp;receives the cleaning mission metadata and parses the format to Amazon DynamoDB. Amazon Kinesis batches the mission data and stores it in <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot"><u><b>Amazon S3</b></u></a>. Amazon S3 is used as the iRobot data lake for analytics, where all message data is compressed and stored. Once the data is in Amazon S3, iRobot uses the AWS Analytics toolset. <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/athena/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot"><u><b>Amazon Athena</b></u></a> allows iRobot to explore and discover patterns in the data without having to run compute resources all the time.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-5" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-5" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-5.ed3895334fc7d02389078d72c62ca1d0efb80eb7.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Data_Correlation" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Data Correlation</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">The cleaning mission is stored in <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/dynamodb/?hp=tile&amp;story=irobot" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon DynamoDB</u></b></a> and linked to a specific robot and consumer.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img alt="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-6" title="PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-6" src="./awsamazoncom_files/PI-iRobot-Mobile_Step-6.05073fff733d440e7118c3c325173744153bf6ce.png">
                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:90px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Customer_Notification" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> Customer Notification</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">The consumer gets an alert that informs them of a successful Roomba 900 series cleaning mission.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </li>

                                    <h2 id="BP_Improves_Effectiveness_and_Gains_Cost_Agility_and_Speed_for_Its_Critical_Business_Apps" class="lb-tiny-align-left lb-txt-normal lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-txt-28 lb-h2 lb-title"> BP Improves Effectiveness and Gains Cost Agility and Speed for Its Critical Business Apps</h2>
                                    <div class="lb-tiny-align-left lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-txt-16 lb-txt-lead lb-txt">
                                        See how BP simplified and modernized its suite of SAP applications, improving user experience while gaining cost agility and enhanced performance.
                                    </div>
                                    <a class="lb-txt-bold lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-txt-16 lb-txt-lead lb-txt" style="margin-top:15px; margin-bottom:15px;" href="https://aws.amazon.com/solutions/case-studies/bp/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"> Learn More&nbsp;<i class="icon-angle-double-right"></i></a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="lb-col lb-tiny-24 lb-mid-12">
                                    <div class="lb-tiny-hide lb-small-hide lb-mid-hide lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-box" style="height: 450px;">
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lb-none-pad lb-none-v-margin lb-grid" style="background-color:#232f3e;">
                            <div class="lb-row lb-row-max-large lb-snap">
                                <div class="lb-col lb-tiny-24 lb-mid-24">
                                    <div class="lb-tiny-hide lb-small-hide lb-mid-hide lb-large-show lb-xlarge-show lb-none-v-margin lb-bodymovin" style="margin-top:30px;" data-loop="false" data-viewport="true" data-path="//d1.awsstatic.com/webteam/homepage/powering-innovation/BP_1200.adc0c18be2ab63d93b5f1cabc2be728b29c9ddcd.json" data-lb-comp="bodymovin-animation" data-lb-comp-registered="true">
                                        <div class="lb-none-pad">
                                            <div class="lb-bm-animation">

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Managing_Critical_Business_Apps" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title"> Managing Critical Business Apps</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">BP's IT organization manages SAP applications used by thousands of employees worldwide for supply chain, procurement, finance, and more.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">

                                                    </div>

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Improving_Speed_.26_Cost_Agility" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Improving Speed &amp; Cost Agility</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">To improve speed and gain cost agility, BP used <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon EC2</u></b></a> to migrate these core business apps to the cloud. In addition, the team built EC2 X1 instances to increase scale and to power their real-time analytics.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">
                                                    <div>

                                                    </div>
                                                </figure>
                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Increasing_Performance" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Increasing Performance</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">The team can now stand up systems on demand in hours instead of weeks or months. BP is seeing performance increases across the board, including a 40 percent speed improvement for the Lubricants ERP system.&nbsp;</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="lb-xbcol">
                                                <figure class="lb-small-show lb-mid-show lb-large-hide lb-xlarge-hide lb-img">

                                                    </div>

                                                <div class="lb-none-pad lb-box" style="height:80px;">
                                                    <h4 id="Securing_Data" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-none lb-txt-white lb-none-v-margin lb-h4 lb-title" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> Securing Data</h4>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="lb-txt-white lb-txt-13 lb-none-v-margin lb-rtxt" style="margin-bottom:30px;">
                                                    <p style="text-align: center;">As part of its cloud migration, BP reset its security standards using <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/config/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Config</u></b></a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/iam/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM)</u></b></a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudwatch/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"><b><u>Amazon CloudWatch</u></b></a>, and <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/trustedadvisor/?hp=tile&amp;story=bp" target="_blank"><b><u>AWS Trusted Advisor</u></b></a>. These new standards helped BP to develop a secure framework for operating its IT organization.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>

                <h2 id="Find._Buy._Deploy." class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-normal lb-txt-none lb-txt-36 lb-small-v-margin lb-h2 lb-title" style="margin-top:0px;"> Find. Buy. Deploy.</h2>
                <div class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-20 lb-small-v-margin lb-txt" style="margin-top:0px;">

                <h2 id="Global_Network_of_AWS_Regions" class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-normal lb-txt-none lb-txt-36 lb-small-v-margin lb-h2 lb-title" style="margin-top:0px;"> Global Network of AWS Regions</h2>
                <div class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-light lb-txt-none lb-txt-20 lb-txt">
                    The AWS Cloud spans 57 Availability Zones within 19 geographic Regions around the world, with announced plans for 15 more Availability Zones and five more Regions in Bahrain, Cape Town, Hong Kong SAR, Milan, and Stockholm

                        <a class="lb-tiny-align-center lb-txt-normal lb-txt-lead lb-txt" href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/"> Learn More <i class="icon-angle-double-right"></i></a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="m-gi-map-pin" data-directory-id="gi-map-pins">
                        <script type="text/x-handlebars-template">
                            {{#each items}}
                            <div class="m-gi-pin-detail-box lb-popover lb-popover-aui lb-popover-mid-small {{#if (strToBool additionalFields.isNew)}}.m-new{{/if}}" data-id="m-gi-pin-popover-{{@index}}" data-action="hover" data-position="left-top" data-lb-comp="popover">
                                {{#if (strToBool additionalFields.isNew)}}
                                <span>New</span> {{/if}}
                                <h2>{{additionalFields.pinName}}</h2>
                                <p>{{additionalFields.pinDescription}}</p>
                                <p>{{cleanText additionalFields.pinBodyText}}</p>
                            </div>
                            {{/each}}
                        </script>
                        <div class="m-gi-map-pin-details-container">

                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="m-gi-map-area-details" data-directory-id="gi-map-areas">
                        <script type="text/x-handlebars-template">
                            <section>
                                {{#each items}}
                                <div class="m-gi-area-detail-box lb-border-p lb-box lb-box-pw" data-id="{{additionalFields.areaId}}">
                                    <span class="icon-close"></span>
                                    <h2>{{additionalFields.areaName}}</h2> {{{additionalFields.areaDescription}}} {{#if additionalFields.edgeLocations}}
                                    <h4>Edge Locations:</h4>
                                    <p>{{additionalFields.edgeLocations}}</p>
                                    {{/if}} {{#if additionalFields.regionalEdgeCaches}}
                                    <h4>Regional Edge Caches:</h4>
                                    <p>{{additionalFields.regionalEdgeCaches}}</p>
                                    {{/if}} {{#if additionalFields.localRegions}}
                                    <h4>Local Regions:</h4>
                                    <p>{{additionalFields.localRegions}}</p>
                                    {{/if}}
                                    <a href="/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/">See detailed list of offerings at all AWS locations</a>
                                </div>
                                {{/each}}
                            </section>
                        </script>
                        <div class="m-gi-map-area-details-container">
                            <section>
                                <div class="m-gi-area-detail-box lb-border-p lb-box lb-box-pw" data-id="apac">
                                    <span class="icon-close"></span>
                                    <h2>Asia Pacific</h2>
                                    <p>The AWS Cloud in Asia Pacific has 26 Availability Zones within seven geographic Regions and one Local Region, with 34 Edge Network locations and five Regional Edge Cache locations.</p>

                                    <h4>Edge Locations:</h4>
                                    <p>Bangalore, India; Chennai, India (2); Hong Kong SAR, China (3); Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia; Manila, the Philippines; Melbourne, Australia; Mumbai, India (2); New Delhi, India; Osaka, Japan; Perth, Australia; Seoul, Korea (4); Singapore (3); Sydney, Australia; Taipei, Taiwan (3); Tokyo, Japan (9)</p>
                                    <h4>Regional Edge Caches:</h4>
                                    <p>Mumbai, India; Seoul, Korea; Singapore; Sydney, Australia; Tokyo, Japan</p>
                                    <h4>Local Regions:</h4>
                                    <p>Osaka</p>
                                    <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/">See detailed list of offerings at all AWS locations</a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="m-gi-area-detail-box lb-border-p lb-box lb-box-pw" data-id="emea">
                                    <span class="icon-close"></span>
                                    <h2>Europe / Middle East / Africa</h2>
                                    <p>The AWS Cloud in Europe, Middle East and Africa has 12 Availability Zones within four geographic Regions, with 39 Edge Network locations and two Regional Edge Cache locations.</p>

                                    <h4>Edge Locations:</h4>
                                    <p>Amsterdam, The Netherlands (2); Berlin, Germany; Cape Town, South Africa; Dublin, Ireland; Frankfurt, Germany (8); Helsinki, Finland; Johannesburg, South Africa; London, England (7); Madrid, Spain (2); Manchester, England; Marseille, France; Milan, Italy; Munich, Germany; Palermo, Italy; Paris, France (3); Prague, Czech Republic; Stockholm, Sweden (3); Vienna, Austria; Warsaw, Poland; Zurich, Switzerland</p>
                                    <h4>Regional Edge Caches:</h4>
                                    <p>Frankfurt, Germany; London, England</p>
                                    <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/">See detailed list of offerings at all AWS locations</a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="m-gi-area-detail-box lb-border-p lb-box lb-box-pw" data-id="sa">
                                    <span class="icon-close"></span>
                                    <h2>South America</h2>
                                    <p>The AWS Cloud in South America has 3 Availability Zones within one geographic Region, with four Edge Network locations and one Regional Edge Cache location.</p>

                                    <h4>Edge Locations:</h4>
                                    <p>Rio de Janeiro (2), Brazil; Sao Paulo, Brazil (2)</p>
                                    <h4>Regional Edge Caches:</h4>
                                    <p>Sao Paulo, Brazil</p>
                                    <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/">See detailed list of offerings at all AWS locations</a>
                                </div>
                                <div class="m-gi-area-detail-box lb-border-p lb-box lb-box-pw" data-id="na">
                                    <span class="icon-close"></span>
                                    <h2>North America</h2>
                                    <p>The AWS Cloud in North America has 20 Availability Zones within six geographic Regions, with 44 Edge Network locations and two Regional Edge Cache locations.</p>

                                    <h4>Edge Locations:</h4>
                                    <p>Ashburn, VA (3); Atlanta GA (3); Boston, MA; Chicago, IL (2); Dallas/Fort Worth, TX (5); Denver, CO (2); Hayward, CA; Jacksonville, FL; Los Angeles, CA (4); Miami, FL (3); Minneapolis, MN; Montreal, QC; New York, NY (3); Newark, NJ (3); Palo Alto, CA; Phoenix, AZ; Philadelphia, PA; San Jose, CA (2); Seattle, WA (3); South Bend, IN; St. Louis, MO; Toronto, ON</p>
                                    <h4>Regional Edge Caches:</h4>
                                    <p>Northern Virginia; Ohio; Oregon</p>
                                    <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/">See detailed list of offerings at all AWS locations</a>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
